config BR2_PACKAGE_GOKE_SNS_BBI2C
	bool "goke-sns-bbi2c"
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_GOKE_OSDRV_GK7205V200
	help
	  Bit-bang (GPIO) i2c sensor bring-up for gk7205v200 boards whose
	  image sensor is wired to GPIO pins instead of the SoC hardware
	  i2c controller (e.g. CP Plus CP-UNC-TA21L2C / Dahua-OEM cameras
	  with a SmartSens SC223A, chip-id 0xcb3e).

	  Builds a small kernel module that registers a software i2c
	  adapter on GPIO7_2 (SDA) / GPIO7_3 (SCL), drives the sensor
	  reset/enable line (GPIO8_7) high, sets the 27 MHz MCLK and holds
	  the MIPI-RX reference clock stable, and ships an init script that
	  points majestic's libsns at the bit-bang bus.

	  Addresses the "sensor i2c never ACKs" class of devices:
	  OpenIPC/firmware issues #1930 and #1404.
